section.p:
“Listen to me now. 
      Iam the one who has traveled the black void between the stars to come to you; 
      Iam the one who has wandered the white void, the plain that stretches its hand between the worlds of the living and the dead; 
      Iam the one who has spoken with the spirits of the ancestors in the sacred stones. 
      Iam the one who came amongst you and learned, like a child, the ways of my tribe; 
      Iam the one who left, like a ghost, when I had learned all I needed; and 
      Iam the one who survived winter alone on Tehuantepec, and who returns to you now.”
